title.rendered: Wimbledon: Ons Jabeur reaches maiden Grand Slam semi-final after 3-set battle vs Marie Bouzkova

content.rendered:
Wimbledon: WTA’s top two ranking star Ons Jabeur reaches maiden Grand Slam Semi-final after defeating Marie Bouzkova in three set (3-6, 6-1, 6-1) battle at Centre Court in Wimbledon. On July 5th evening Both entered into court likelihood to get semi-final ticket. When match start, Bouzkova was in attacking form and played brilliantly, she reserved first set with 6-3 score. No one knows Czech Tennis star will lose the match.

At the start of second set, it was a do-or-lose situation for Ons Jabeur, thatswhy she made a sudden move to offensive start to beat Bouzkova. Her decision was right and she scored 6-1 in second set. Bouzkova lost final set also with 1-6. Finally Jabeur reached maiden Grand Slam Semi-Final.

It was very exciting moment when Jabeur turned to equal score after beating Bouzkova in 2nd set. The heartbeats of both tennis star supporter had increased when 3rd set started. Every one was worried about winning of their favourite player. Following her sudden attacking move in second set Jabeur make a ful stop on which side camel sit. Jebeur supporters celebrated of her tough winning.

Jebuer supporter across told to reporter, “They Extremely hope She will enter into final by defeating T Mariaon, German Tennis Professional on upcoming Thursday. The semi-final to be played between both at Centre court at 6:00 pm.

  • Match Result:

          M. Bouzkova   vs      Ons Jabeur

          6, 1, 1                         3, 6, 6

  • Grand Slam First Semi-Final Match (Women’s Single) to be played on July 7th between Ons Jabeur and Tatzana Maria at Centre court at 6:00 pm.

Read more: England Cricket Trolls Virat Kohli After Edgbaston Victory, And It Has A Jonny Bairstow Reference
